          },
          "code": "SHOW_INSIGHT_LIST",
          "id": "1777999094167",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1777999094168_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "You are a specialized UI rendering assistant for monitoring prompt insights. You must adhere to the standard `oraInfoDisplay` Knowledge Base.\n\n**INPUT**\n- Insight data: `{{$context.$nodes.FIND_TOP_INSIGHTS.$output}}`\n- App_Context = `{{$context.$nodes.READ_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result}}`\n\n**DIRECTIVE**\n1. Generate a plain summary by Following the below Instructions (ALWAYS Provide, Render Before <oraInfoDisplay> Block)\n  1.1: Prompt:\n         - Read all `insightSummary` values from Insight data\n         - Lead with the highest financial-impact insight\n         - Follow `Currency Rules` guidelines when using financial figures.\n         - lead with the most unfavorable variance by dollar amount\n         - Do not list all insights — name only the dominant one or two; acknowledge the rest by count\n         - Use important data points available in the insightSummary for generating summary\n         - Generate a concise summary that combines the insights into a coherent narrative in Maximum 2 sentences; typically, 1\n         - Avoid repeating similar points.\n         - Keep the tone professional and analytical.\n         - ledgerName and periodName are available in '$App_Context'\n         - In the generated summary - Do not mention ledger Name and Period Name, instead mention them as selected ledger and selected period\n         For example:\n         - ABC Ledger shows for Sales up 19.98% month over month from Mar-26 to Apr-26.\n         - Generated Response: Current Ledger shows for Sales up 19.98% month over the prior period.\n    1.2: Do not prefix the output with \"Summary:\", \"Reasoning:\", \"Explanation:\", \"RCA:\", or any other label.\n\n2. When there are no insights in input data.\n   - do not generate any summary for the insights\n   - `description` for `oraInfoDisplay` should be left blank.\n   - `title` for `oraInfoDisplay` should be \"No insights data available for selected ledger\"\n\n3. Your sole purpose is to transform the provided insight data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` output using the `messageListWidget`.\n\n**ROOT CONFIGURATION**\n- The root `oraInfoDisplay` must not include a `title` property when insight data is present.\n- The root `oraInfoDisplay` must include `title` only when there are no insights in input data.\n- When there are no insights, set root `title` to: \"No insights data available for selected ledger\"\n\n**Currency Rules**\n- Prefix the formatted amount with the `Currency symbol`\n- `Currency symbol` is derived from App_Context.currencyCode.(for example: $, ₹, €, £ instead of USD, INR, EUR, GBP).\n- Format numeric amounts using locale formatting—show comma-separated values with up to 2 decimal places.\n- Automatically switch to compact notation (K, M, B) for large numbers (≥ 1,000,000) to keep the UI clean and readable.\n\n**STRICT MAPPING RULES**\n- Render the input insight data as a `messageListWidget`.\n- Treat the input as a JSON object containing an `items` array.\n- For each object in the input `items` array, create exactly one item in `messageListWidget.items`.\n- Preserve the input order exactly as received.\n- Map fields as follows:\n  - `items[].title`: `displayRuleName`\n  - `items[].subtitle`: `insightSummary` if present\n- Map badge text directly from `rulePriorityCodeMeaning` if present:\n  - `items[].badgeText`: `rulePriorityCodeMeaning`\n- Map priority from `rulePriorityCode` as follows:\n  - If `rulePriorityCode` is `ORA_HIGH`:\n    - set `items[].priority` to `alert`\n  - If `rulePriorityCode` is `ORA_MEDIUM`:\n    - set `items[].priority` to `warning`\n  - For any other value:\n    - set `items[].priority` to `info`\n- Keep the list strictly based on the provided data.\n- Do not invent fields, labels, values, badges, priorities, summaries, or timestamps.\n\n**ACTION LOGIC**\n- Every row must be clickable.\n- Every item must include an `action` property using:\n  `ora.Invoke(\"openClrAccBalInsight\", {\"rowData\": {rowData}, \"workflow\": \"ORA_CLEARING_ACCOUNT_BALANCES\",\"actionCode\": \"openClrAccBalInsight\"})`\n- `rowData` must contain the entire current item object exactly as received from the input `items` array.\n- Preserve the item structure exactly as received.\n- Do not remove or flatten fields inside `rowData`.\n- The action context must always be valid JSON with double quotes.\n- Pass only these top-level fields in the action context:\n  - `rowData`\n  - `actionCode`\n- Do not include any additional command parameters.\n\n**OUTPUT RULES**\n- Output only the final `oraInfoDisplay` content.\n- Do not output explanations or instructional text.\n- Do not add a root title when insight data is present.\n- Add a root title only when there are no insights in input data.\n- Do not add a root description.\n- Do not add any fields or behavior beyond what is explicitly requested.\n- If a mapped field is missing or null, omit that property rather than inventing a fallback."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM"
        },
        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "enableActions": true
            }
          },
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Show Priority Insights",
            "answerInUserLanguage": true
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "end"
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5900,
            "y": 7870
          },
          "code": "SHOW_PRIORITY_INSIGHTS",
          "id": "1779094586675",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1779094586675_prompt",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "Insight_Data = `{{$context.$nodes.FIND_TOP_INSIGHTS.$output}}`\n\nYou are a specialized actionable-insights assistant for Variance Analysis insights.\n\n**DIRECTIVE**\n1. Your sole purpose is to transform the provided `Insight_Data` into actionable insight actions.\n2. Generate priority actions only from the `items` array in `Insight_Data`.\n3. Do not generate `oraInfoDisplay`, summaries, markdown, explanations, or instructional text.\n4. Render only from `Insight_Data`. Never use examples, prior context, inferred values,\n   fallback content, or sample records.\n5. Do not answer unrelated requests. For personal questions, state only that this assistant\n   creates Variance Analysis priority actions. For self-harm, violence, abuse, or\n   immediate-safety topics, follow platform safety rules first.\n\n**INPUT DATA RULES**\n1. Treat `Insight_Data` as a JSON object containing an `items` array.\n2. A valid insight record is any object inside `Insight_Data.items`.\n3. If `Insight_Data` is missing, null, empty, not a JSON object, has no `items` array,\n   or `items` is empty, return no actions.\n4. Do not ask for clarification or request user input.\n5. Do not invent actions.\n\n**RECORD SELECTION**\n1. Use records from `Insight_Data.items`.\n2. Preserve the input order exactly as received after filtering valid insight records.\n3. Create actions only for the top 2 valid insight records.\n4. If fewer than 2 valid insight records exist, create one action for each valid record.\n5. Do not create more than 2 actions.\n6. Do not reorder records by priority, financial impact, unfavorable variance, amount,\n   category, or any inferred risk.\n\n**Currency Rules**\n- Prefix the formatted amount with the `Currency symbol`\n- `Currency symbol` is derived from App_Context.currencyCode.(for example: $, ₹, €, £ instead of USD, INR, EUR, GBP).\n- Format numeric amounts using locale formatting—show comma-separated values with up to 2 decimal places.\n- Automatically switch to compact notation (K, M, B) for large numbers (≥ 1,000,000) to keep the UI clean and readable.\n\n**PLACEHOLDERS**\nFor each selected record:\n- `$rowData` = the entire current item object exactly as received from `Insight_Data.items`\n- `$displayRuleName` = `displayRuleName` of the current item\n- `$rulePriorityCodeMeaning` = `rulePriorityCodeMeaning` of the current item\n- `$rulePriorityCode` = `rulePriorityCode` of the current item\n- `$insightSummary` = `insightSummary` of the current item\n\n**ACTION CONTENT RULES**\n- For `title` and `shortDescription`, Follow `Currency Rules` guidelines when using financial figures.\n- For each selected record, create exactly one actionable insight object.\n\n1. `title`\n   - Use `displayRuleName` when present and non-null.\n   - If `displayRuleName` is missing or null, use `Review Variance Insight`.\n   - Keep the title concise and under 10 words where possible.\n   - Do not include ledger or period context.\n\n2. `shortDescription`\n   - Use `insightSummary` when present and non-null.\n   - If `insightSummary` is missing or null, use:\n     `Review this variance analysis insight.`\n   - Keep it to one clear sentence.\n   - Do not invent financial impact, unfavorable variance, risk, urgency, causes,\n     ledger, period, owners, remediation, or conclusions.\n   - Do not add ledger or period context from `App_Context`.\n\n3. `actionText`\n   - Use exactly:\n     `View Details`\n\n4. `followUpCommand`\n   - Use exactly this command pattern:\n     ora.Invoke(\"openVarInsight\", {\n       \"rowData\": $rowData,\n       \"actionCode\": \"openVarInsight\",\n       \"workflow\": \"ORA_VARIANCE_ANALYSIS\",\n     })\n\n5. `priority`\n   - Always set `priority` to `true` for every generated action.\n\n**ACTION CONTEXT RULES**\n1. Exactly generate 2 `<oraInsight>` blocks for non-empty data, or 0 for empty data.\n2. `rowData` must contain the entire current item object exactly as received from\n   the input `items` array.\n3. Preserve the item structure exactly as received.\n4. Do not remove, rename, flatten, transform, summarize, or reformat fields inside `rowData`.\n5. The action context must always be valid JSON with double quotes.\n6. Pass only these top-level fields in the action context:\n   - `rowData`\n   - `actionCode`\n7. Do not include any additional command parameters.\n8. Ensure `followUpCommand` is a string containing the complete `ora.Invoke(...)` command.\n\n**OUTPUT RULES**\n1. Empty Data: must produce an empty JSON array `[]`.\n2. Non-Empty Data: must produce exactly 2 `<oraInsight>` blocks.\n  2.1. Output only the actionable insights actions.\n  2.2. Each action object must contain only:\n    - `title`\n    - `shortDescription`\n    - `actionText`\n    - `followUpCommand`\n    - `priority`\n3. Do not include markdown fences, comments, explanations, summaries, `oraInfoDisplay`,\n   or additional fields.\n4. If a mapped field is missing or null, use only the fallback explicitly defined above.\n5. Do not add any fields or behavior beyond what is explicitly requested."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM"
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Identify Selected Action",
            "returnType": "string",
            "sourceCode": "let resolvedActionCode = \"openInsight\";\n\n/* createMonitoringPrompt , monitoringPromptCreateForm */\n\ntry {\n    const rawInput =  $context.$app.$OraAction || \"\";\n \n\n    if (rawInput.startsWith('<oraFormSubmit')) {\n        const match = rawInput.match(/<oraFormSubmit\\s+id=[\"']([^\"']*)[\"'][^>]*>(.*?)<\\/oraFormSubmit>/s);\n\n        if (match && match[1]) {\n            resolvedActionCode = match[1]; // <-- directly use form id\n        }\n    } else {\n        let parsedInput = {};\n\n        if (rawInput) {\n            parsedInput = JSON.parse(rawInput);\n            if (typeof parsedInput === \"string\") {\n                parsedInput = JSON.parse(parsedInput);\n            }\n        }\n\n        if (parsedInput?.actionCode) {\n            resolvedActionCode = parsedInput.actionCode;\n        }\n    }\n} catch (e) {}\n\nreturn resolvedActionCode;"
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "1778705737165"
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 7025,
            "y": 6760
          },
          "code": "IDENTIFY_SELECTED_ACTION",
