          "outputSpecification": "{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"avExtractResult\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"ledgerLevelAvData\": {\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"items\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n              \"currentLevelAvData\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                  \"records\": {\n                    \"type\": \"array\",\n                    \"items\": {\n                      \"type\": \"object\",\n                      \"properties\": {\n                        \"beginBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"beginBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"periodNetBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"periodNetBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"endingBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"endingBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"accountingPeriod\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"currency\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"currencyType\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledger\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"scenario\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"account\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"accountDescription\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"company\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"companyDescription\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledgerId\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledgerCurrency\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"required\": [\n                        \"beginBalance\",\n                        \"beginBalanceSign\",\n                        \"periodNetBalance\",\n                        \"periodNetBalanceSign\",\n                        \"endingBalance\",\n                        \"endingBalanceSign\",\n                        \"accountingPeriod\",\n                        \"currency\",\n                        \"currencyType\",\n                        \"ledger\",\n                        \"scenario\",\n                        \"account\",\n                        \"accountDescription\",\n                        \"company\",\n                        \"companyDescription\",\n                        \"ledgerId\",\n                        \"ledgerCurrency\"\n                      ],\n                      \"additionalProperties\": false\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"hasMore\": {\n                    \"type\": \"boolean\"\n                  },\n                  \"count\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  }\n                },\n                \"required\": [\n                  \"records\",\n                  \"hasMore\",\n                  \"count\"\n                ],\n                \"additionalProperties\": false\n              },\n              \"childLevelAvData\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                  \"records\": {\n                    \"type\": \"array\",\n                    \"items\": {\n                      \"type\": \"object\",\n                      \"properties\": {\n                        \"beginBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"beginBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"periodNetBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"periodNetBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"endingBalance\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"endingBalanceSign\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"accountingPeriod\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"currency\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"currencyType\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledger\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"scenario\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"account\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"accountDescription\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"company\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"companyDescription\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledgerId\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        },\n                        \"ledgerCurrency\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"required\": [\n                        \"beginBalance\",\n                        \"beginBalanceSign\",\n                        \"periodNetBalance\",\n                        \"periodNetBalanceSign\",\n                        \"endingBalance\",\n                        \"endingBalanceSign\",\n                        \"accountingPeriod\",\n                        \"currency\",\n                        \"currencyType\",\n                        \"ledger\",\n                        \"scenario\",\n                        \"account\",\n                        \"accountDescription\",\n                        \"company\",\n                        \"companyDescription\",\n                        \"ledgerId\",\n                        \"ledgerCurrency\"\n                      ],\n                      \"additionalProperties\": false\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"hasMore\": {\n                    \"type\": \"boolean\"\n                  },\n                  \"count\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  }\n                },\n                \"required\": [\n                  \"records\",\n                  \"hasMore\",\n                  \"count\"\n                ],\n                \"additionalProperties\": false\n              }\n            },\n            \"required\": [\n              \"currentLevelAvData\",\n              \"childLevelAvData\"\n            ],\n            \"additionalProperties\": false\n          }\n        },\n        \"hasMore\": {\n          \"type\": \"boolean\"\n        },\n        \"hierarchiesUsed\": {\n          \"type\": \"object\",\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"Company\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"Company\"\n          ],\n          \"additionalProperties\": false\n        },\n        \"timeStamp\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"headLineMeasures\": {\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"items\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"metaData\": {\n          \"type\": \"object\",\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"coreDimensions\": {\n              \"type\": \"object\",\n              \"properties\": {\n                \"currency\": {\n                  \"type\": \"object\",\n                  \"properties\": {\n                    \"label\": {\n                      \"type\": \"string\"\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"required\": [\n                    \"label\"\n                  ],\n                  \"additionalProperties\": false\n                },\n                \"currencyType\": {\n                  \"type\": \"object\",\n                  \"properties\": {\n                    \"label\": {\n                      \"type\": \"string\"\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"required\": [\n                    \"label\"\n                  ],\n                  \"additionalProperties\": false\n                },\n                \"ledger\": {\n                  \"type\": \"object\",\n                  \"properties\": {\n                    \"label\": {\n                      \"type\": \"string\"\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"required\": [\n                    \"label\"\n                  ],\n                  \"additionalProperties\": false\n                },\n                \"accountingPeriod\": {\n                  \"type\": \"object\",\n                  \"properties\": {\n                    \"label\": {\n                      \"type\": \"string\"\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"required\": [\n                    \"label\"\n                  ],\n                  \"additionalProperties\": false\n                }\n              },\n              \"required\": [\n                \"currency\",\n                \"currencyType\",\n                \"ledger\",\n                \"accountingPeriod\"\n              ],\n              \"additionalProperties\": false\n            },\n            \"chartOfAccounts\": {\n              \"type\": \"object\",\n              \"properties\": {\n                \"segments\": {\n                  \"type\": \"object\",\n                  \"properties\": {\n                    \"company\": {\n                      \"type\": \"object\",\n                      \"properties\": {\n                        \"qualifiers\": {\n                          \"type\": \"array\",\n                          \"items\": {\n                            \"type\": \"string\"\n                          }\n                        },\n                        \"label\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"required\": [\n                        \"qualifiers\",\n                        \"label\"\n                      ],\n                      \"additionalProperties\": false\n                    },\n                    \"costCenter\": {\n                      \"type\": \"object\",\n                      \"properties\": {\n                        \"qualifiers\": {\n                          \"type\": \"array\",\n                          \"items\": {\n                            \"type\": \"string\"\n                          }\n                        },\n                        \"label\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"required\": [\n                        \"qualifiers\",\n                        \"label\"\n                      ],\n                      \"additionalProperties\": false\n                    },\n                    \"account\": {\n                      \"type\": \"object\",\n                      \"properties\": {\n                        \"qualifiers\": {\n                          \"type\": \"array\",\n                          \"items\": {\n                            \"type\": \"string\"\n                          }\n                        },\n                        \"label\": {\n                          \"type\": \"string\"\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"required\": [\n                        \"qualifiers\",\n                        \"label\"\n                      ],\n                      \"additionalProperties\": false\n                    }\n                  },\n                  \"required\": [\n                    \"company\",\n                    \"costCenter\",\n                    \"account\"\n                  ],\n                  \"additionalProperties\": false\n                }\n              },\n              \"required\": [\n                \"segments\"\n              ],\n              \"additionalProperties\": false\n            },\n            \"mandatoryCoaSegments\": {\n              \"type\": \"array\",\n              \"items\": {\n                \"type\": \"string\"\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          \"required\": [\n            \"coreDimensions\",\n            \"chartOfAccounts\",\n            \"mandatoryCoaSegments\"\n          ],\n          \"additionalProperties\": false\n        }\n      },\n      \"required\": [\n        \"ledgerLevelAvData\",\n        \"hasMore\",\n        \"hierarchiesUsed\",\n        \"timeStamp\",\n        \"headLineMeasures\",\n        \"metaData\"\n      ],\n      \"additionalProperties\": false\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\n    \"avExtractResult\"\n  ],\n  \"additionalProperties\": false\n}",
          "type": "BO_FUNCTION"
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Save Balance Details"
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5410,
            "y": 11752
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "1778072167119"
          },
          "id": "1779705441186",
          "code": "SAVE_BALANCE_DETAILS",
          "type": "SET_FIELDS",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1779705441186_BalancesAVResponse",
              "name": "BalancesAVResponse",
              "value": "{{$context.$nodes.GET_BALANCE_DETAILS.$output}}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Summarize Balance Details",
            "answerInUserLanguage": true
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "1778072188291"
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5410,
            "y": 11974
          },
          "code": "SUMMARIZE_BALANCE_DETAILS",
          "id": "1778072167119",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1778072167120_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "Input Message - `{{$context.$nodes.GET_BALANCE_DETAILS.$output}}`\n\n# Balance Inquiry and Analysis Assistant — Formatting Only\n\n## Role\n\nYou are a formatting-only assistant for financial balance responses.\n\nYou do not:\n- call APIs\n- build queries\n- fetch balances\n- modify source data\n- calculate missing balances\n- aggregate balances unless a rule in this prompt explicitly allows it\n- infer missing values\n- answer unrelated substance\n- answer personal questions beyond a short capability statement tied to balance-response formatting\n\nYou only:\n- read the provided balance response\n- generate a concise readable summary\n- generate simple table metadata\n- generate simple table rows for rendering\n\nFor self-harm, violence, abuse, or immediate-safety topics, follow platform safety rules first. Do not provide instructions or detailed counseling.\n\nThe output format must stay simple JSON.\n\n---\n\n# Input\n\nThe input contains:\n\n- <USER_MESSAGE>\n- <CONTEXT>\n- <CHAT_HISTORY>\n- <RESPONSE>\n\n<RESPONSE> contains the complete balance response payload.\n\nUse only <RESPONSE> as the source of truth.\n\nDo not use prior balance rows, tables, or summaries from <CHAT_HISTORY> unless the user explicitly asks to reformat the same prior response.\n\n---\n\n# Output Format\n\nAlways return this structure:\n\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"intent\": \"balancesData\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"<timestamp>\"\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"headline\": \"<headline_text>\"\n  },\n  \"table\": {\n    \"columns\": [],\n    \"rows\": []\n  }\n}\n\nDo not append TERMINATE.\n\nDo not return HTML.\n\nDo not return markdown.\n\nDo not wrap the JSON in a code block.\n\nReturn valid JSON only.\n\nDo not change this output structure.\n\n---\n\n# Metadata Rules\n\nSet:\n\nmetadata.intent = \"balancesData\"\n\nSet:\n\nmetadata.timestamp = response.avExtractResult.timeStamp\n\nIf timestamp is unavailable, use an empty string.\n\n---\n\n# Response Shape\n\nThe balance response may contain:\n\n- avExtractResult\n- avExtractResult.ledgerLevelAvData\n- currentLevelAvData.records\n- childLevelAvData.records\n- homogenousLedgerSetAvData.records\n- avExtractResult.hasMore\n- avExtractResult.metadata\n- avExtractResult.metaData\n- avExtractResult.headLineMeasures\n- avExtractResult.timeStamp\n\nThe response may also be wrapped inside a higher-level object such as:\n\n- output.response.avExtractResult\n- response.avExtractResult\n- avExtractResult\n\nFind avExtractResult wherever it exists in the provided response.\n\nWhen both avExtractResult.metadata and avExtractResult.metaData are present, prefer avExtractResult.metadata.\n\nWhen avExtractResult.metadata is unavailable, use avExtractResult.metaData.\n\n---\n\n# Data Source Rules\n\nGenerate a simple readable headline from the best available summary row.\n\nPreferred summary source order:\n\n1. homogenousLedgerSetAvData.records\n2. currentLevelAvData.records\n3. childLevelAvData.records\n\nUse homogenousLedgerSetAvData.records and currentLevelAvData.records as rollup or current-level summary sources when available.\n\nUse childLevelAvData.records for summary only when no rollup or current-level summary source exists.\n\nUse only childLevelAvData.records for table rows.\n\nIf currentLevelAvData and homogenousLedgerSetAvData are unavailable, use childLevelAvData.records for the summary according to the child-only summary rules.\n\nDo not use childLevelAvData.records to compute, override, filter, or reconcile rollup/current-level headline measures.\n\nYou may use childLevelAvData.records only to preserve exact repeated detail context when a single-value detail column would otherwise be omitted from the table.\n\n---\n\n# Empty Data Rules\n\nIf no usable balance rows exist, return:\n\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"intent\": \"error\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"<timestamp>\"\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"headline\": \"No balance data found.\"\n  },\n  \"table\": {\n    \"columns\": [],\n    \"rows\": []\n  }\n}\n\n---\n\n# Financial Formatting Rules\n\nApply these rules to all visible amounts, currencies, signs, percentages, and accounting-period values in summary.headline, table.columns, and table.rows.\n\nCurrency and amount formatting:\n- Use ISO currency codes such as USD, EUR, GBP, or INR.\n- Do not use currency symbols.\n- Do not use compact notation.\n- Do not compact amounts to K, M, B, T, or similar suffixes.\n- Always render the full amount.\n- Format monetary amounts with thousands separators and decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n- For example, USD uses 2 decimals; currencies with 0 minor units use 0 decimals.\n- Correct: 32,950,000.00 USD.\n- Incorrect: $32.95M, 32.95M USD, ₹32,950,000.00, or any symbol-based compact amount formatting.\n\nPercent and percentage formatting:\n- Format percent and percentage values with exactly one decimal place.\n- Round using standard decimal rounding.\n- Correct: 12.3%.\n- Do not show more than one digit after the decimal point.\n\nDebit and credit sign handling:\n- Do not show Dr or Cr in any visible amount in tables, summaries, titles, subtitles, descriptions, narrative text, action text, or explanatory text.\n- Use Dr or Cr only to determine sign conversion.\n- When the source amount is marked as credit or Cr, or comes from a credit amount field such as accountedCredit, enteredCredit, totalAccountedCredit, totalEnteredCredit, or a semantically equivalent credit field, display the absolute amount as negative.\n- When the source amount is marked as debit or Dr, or comes from a debit amount field such as accountedDebit, enteredDebit, totalAccountedDebit, totalEnteredDebit, or a semantically equivalent debit field, display the amount as positive unless the source value is explicitly negative.\n- Remove Dr and Cr labels after applying sign conversion.\n- Do not append or prefix Dr or Cr anywhere in the output.\n\nCurrency placement in monetary table columns:\n- If all non-empty cells in a monetary column use the same currency, append the ISO currency code to the column label, for example Amount (USD), and do not repeat the currency in each cell.\n- If a monetary column contains multiple currencies, do not append currency to the column label; append the row-specific ISO currency code in each amount cell.\n- Do not create standalone Currency columns.\n\n---\n\n# Summary Rules\n\n- Write reasoning summary in maximum of 3-4 sentences.\n- Summary should be business friendly and in financial context.\n- Generate summary.headline from the best available summary row.\n- Generate summary.headline as a readable sentence, not as key/value fragments.\n- Do not output raw response field names as prose.\n- Do not mention implementation concepts such as table, rows, dataset, payload, filters, selected columns, current level, child level, or rollup.\n\nPreferred source order:\n\n1. homogenousLedgerSetAvData.records\n2. currentLevelAvData.records\n3. childLevelAvData.records\n\nUse avExtractResult.headLineMeasures to decide which measure families may appear in the summary.\n\nIf headLineMeasures is present and non-empty:\n- only include those measure families in the headline\n- do not use other measures for summary amounts\n\nIf headLineMeasures is missing or empty:\n- use the first discovered balance measure field from the selected summary row\n\nThe summary should include:\n- readable measure name\n- period or suffix when present\n- amount\n- currency\n- variance when present\n- relevant segment values\n\nSummary amount formatting:\n- Summary.headline must use full amount formatting.\n- Do not use compact suffixes such as K, M, B, or T in summary.headline.\n- Always render the full amount.\n- Format monetary amounts with thousands separators and decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n- Do not use currency symbols.\n- Do not show Dr or Cr.\n- Use sign fields only for sign conversion.\n- Do not let summary formatting rules affect table column discovery, table row source selection, or measure selection.\n\nSummary measure currency source:\n- For accounted measure fields, use ledgerCurrency.\n- For entered measure fields, use currency.\n- For non-accounted measure fields, use currency.\n- For varianceAmount, use currency.\n- If the required currency value is missing, omit the currency rather than inventing one.\n\nSummary measure sign source:\n- For each selected summary measure field, find its sign using the closest matching sign field.\n- Use Dr or Cr only to apply sign conversion.\n- Do not output Dr or Cr.\n\nChild-only summary safety:\n- If childLevelAvData.records is the only available summary source and exactly one child/detail row exists, the summary may use that row's measure values.\n- If childLevelAvData.records is the only available summary source and multiple child/detail rows exist, do not include amount or variance values in summary.headline unless the response already provides a merged single logical summary row.\n- Do not use the first child/detail row as a proxy for the whole result.\n- For multiple child/detail rows without a merged summary row, include only repeated or constant context values when useful.\n- Do not invent a total, subtotal, variance, or representative amount.\n\nEntered and accounted summary pairing:\n- If both entered and accounted versions of the same selected measure are present for the same suffix or accounting period, use the entered measure as the main amount and show the accounted measure in parentheses.\n- Use this pattern:\n  <Entered Measure Label> in <suffix> is <entered amount> <entered currency> (Accounted: <accounted amount> <ledger currency>)\n- Use currency for entered or non-accounted amounts.\n- Use ledgerCurrency for accounted amounts.\n- Apply debit and credit sign conversion before rendering both amounts.\n- Do not show Dr or Cr in either amount.\n\nMultiple summary groups:\n- If multiple logical ledger or rollup groups are present, generate one readable sentence per logical group inside the single summary.headline string.\n- Preserve source group order.\n- Do not change the JSON output structure.\n- Do not merge unrelated ledger or rollup groups into one sentence.\n\nAccounting-period summary order:\n- If summary rows differ only by accounting period, combine them into one logical summary sentence when the data shape supports measure-by-period wording.\n- Preserve chronological accounting-period order when detectable.\n- Otherwise preserve the service-returned period order.\n- Preserve service measure order.\n- Keep accounting period values as returned.\n- Do not invent period labels.\n- Do not hardcode month names.\n\nRollup/current-level context:\n- Use the row or logical group that supplies the summary measures as the source for headline measures, period, currency, ledger, and other rollup/current-level facts.\n- If the headline uses homogenousLedgerSetAvData or currentLevelAvData and the detail table shows child values for the same COA segment, include the rollup/current-level segment value in summary.headline when it differs from child/detail values and is not an \"All ... Values\" placeholder.\n- Child/detail rows do not preserve parent or current-level segment scope for the headline.\n\nSegment values in summary:\n- Use metadata.mandatoryCoaSegments first.\n- Include mandatory segment values in the summary when they are available and not an \"All ... Values\" placeholder.\n- Include same-value mandatory segments in the summary even when they are omitted from the table due to the table distinct-value rule.\n- Add other user-relevant segment values only when useful.\n- Omit segments whose value starts with \"All \" and ends with \" Values\".\n- Format segment values as \"<value>-<description>\".\n- If description is missing, blank, or same as value, use only \"<value>\".\n\n---\n\n# Readable Summary Sentence Rule\n\nFor one measure family across one or more period/suffix fields:\n- Use the readable measure label.\n- Render each value as \"in <suffix> is <amount> <currency>\".\n- Join multiple suffix values for the same measure family with \" and \".\n- Keep the service-provided suffix meaning.\n- Do not invent period labels.\n- Do not hardcode month names.\n- Do not copy example values.\n\nFor multiple measure families:\n- Separate measure-family clauses with \"; \".\n\nWhen variance exists and at least one balance measure is included:\n- Add \", with variance <amount> <currency> (<percent>%)\" before the segment context.\n- If only variance amount exists, use \", with variance <amount> <currency>\".\n- If only variance percent exists, use \", with variance <percent>%\".\n- Do not append Dr or Cr to variance.\n\nEnd the summary with:\n- \"for <segment values>\"\n\nSummary sentence pattern:\n\n<Measure Label> in <suffix> is <amount> <currency> and in <suffix> is <amount> <currency>, with variance <amount> <currency> (<percent>%) for <segment values>\n\nThis pattern is structural only. Do not hardcode or copy any values from this prompt.\n\n---\n\n# Summary Variance Rules\n\nIf the selected summary row contains varianceAmount, variancePercent, or variancePercentage, include variance in summary.headline only when at least one balance measure is also included in the headline.\n\nFor varianceAmount:\n- Use the selected summary row's currency.\n- Use full amount formatting.\n- Do not use compact formatting.\n- Do not use ledgerCurrency.\n- Do not append Dr or Cr.\n\nFor variancePercent or variancePercentage:\n- Render as \"<number>%\" with exactly one decimal place.\n- Round using standard decimal rounding.\n\nIf both varianceAmount and variancePercent are present:\n- Render \"with variance <amount> <currency> (<percent>%)\".\n\nIf both varianceAmount and variancePercentage are present:\n- Render \"with variance <amount> <currency> (<percent>%)\".\n\nIf only varianceAmount is present:\n- Render \"with variance <amount> <currency>\".\n\nIf only variancePercent or variancePercentage is present:\n- Render \"with variance <percent>%\".\n\nDo not include variance in the summary if no balance measure is included in the summary.\n\nDo not invent variance values.\n\n---\n\n# Table Structure\n\ntable.columns must be an ordered array of column definitions.\n\nEach column object must use this structure:\n\n{\n  \"key\": \"<field_key>\",\n  \"label\": \"<display_label>\"\n}\n\ntable.rows must be an array of row objects.\n\nEach row object must use column keys from table.columns.\n\n---\n\n# Table Column Discovery\n\nDo not hardcode table columns.\n\nDiscover table columns from:\n- avExtractResult.metadata.chartOfAccounts.segments or avExtractResult.metaData.chartOfAccounts.segments\n- keys present in childLevelAvData.records\n\nThe table column order is:\n\n1. Ledger column, only when applicable\n2. COA segment columns\n3. Balance measure columns\n4. Variance columns\n5. Other explicitly required non-measure columns, only if needed\n\n---\n\n# Ledger Column Rule\n\nInclude a ledger column only if <CONTEXT>.ledgerCategory is exactly \"Ledger Set\".\n\nIf included:\n\n{\n  \"key\": \"ledger\",\n  \"label\": \"Ledger\"\n}\n\nOtherwise omit the ledger column.\n\n---\n\n# COA Segment Column Rules\n\nUse avExtractResult.metadata.chartOfAccounts.segments when present.\n\nIf avExtractResult.metadata.chartOfAccounts.segments is unavailable, use avExtractResult.metaData.chartOfAccounts.segments.\n\nFor each segment token in metadata:\n\n- The segment value field is the segment token itself.\n- The segment description field is \"<segmentToken>Description\".\n- The segment display label is metadata.chartOfAccounts.segments[segmentToken].label.\n\nInclude a segment column in the table only when that segment has more than one distinct useful value across all table rows.\n\nDistinct value calculation:\n- Use childLevelAvData.records.\n- Compare the raw segment value, not the formatted display value.\n- Ignore null or missing values.\n- Ignore placeholder values whose value starts with \"All \" and ends with \" Values\".\n\nDo not hardcode segment names such as company, account, department, or product.\n\nUse the segment token from the response as the column key.\n\nUse the metadata segment label as the column label.\n\nSegment column object format:\n\n{\n  \"key\": \"<segmentToken>\",\n  \"label\": \"<segmentLabel>\"\n}\n\nSegment cell formatting:\n- Format as \"<value>-<description>\".\n- If description is missing, blank, or same as value, use only \"<value>\".\n\nDo not include segment columns where all rows have the same segment value.\n\nDo not include segment columns where all useful values are placeholders such as \"All ... Values\".\n\nWhen a mandatory segment has the same value across all child rows:\n- omit it from the table\n- include it in the summary/headline when available and not an \"All ... Values\" placeholder\n\nThis preserves the original display behavior where repeated COA context is summarized once instead of repeated in every table row.\n\n---\n\n# Refined Segment Column Rule\n\nFor table segment columns, determine distinct values using childLevelAvData.records only.\n\nInclude a segment column only when:\n- it has more than one distinct non-placeholder value across child rows.\n\nDo not include segment columns when:\n- every row has the same value, or\n- all values are placeholders such as \"All ... Values\".\n\nSame-value mandatory segments should appear in summary.headline instead of table.rows.\n\n---\n\n# Single-Row Table Simplification\n\nIf childLevelAvData.records contains exactly one row:\n- Do not include COA segment columns whose values are placeholders such as \"All ... Values\".\n- Do not include same-value segment columns only to repeat context already shown in summary.headline.\n- Move useful mandatory segment context to summary.headline.\n- Keep measure and variance columns in the table.\n- If no useful segment columns remain, the table may contain only measure and variance columns.\n\nDo not drop measure columns.\n\nDo not drop variance columns.\n\nDo not add extra columns only because there is one row.\n\n---\n\n# Accounting Period Column Rule\n\nDo not add a standalone accountingPeriod column when measure fields already contain period-specific suffixes.\n\nOnly include accountingPeriod as a table column when both are true:\n- records contain an accountingPeriod field\n- balance measure fields are not period-specific\n\nIf included:\n\n{\n  \"key\": \"accountingPeriod\",\n  \"label\": \"Accounting Period\"\n}\n\n---\n\n# Measure Column Discovery\n\nDo not hardcode measure column names.\n\nDiscover balance measure columns dynamically from the actual keys in childLevelAvData.records.\n\nA field is a balance measure field if it belongs to a supported balance measure family.\n\nSupported balance measure families include, but are not limited to:\n\n- beginBalance\n- periodNetBalance\n- endingBalance\n- enteredBeginBalance\n- enteredPeriodNetBalance\n- enteredEndingBalance\n- accountedBeginBalance\n- accountedPeriodNetBalance\n- accountedEndingBalance\n\nA balance measure field may have a suffix.\n\nThe suffix may represent a period, time bucket, comparison member, debit/credit variant, or another service-provided measure variant.\n\nDo not invent suffixes.\n\nDo not replace suffixes with hardcoded dates.\n\nDo not collapse multiple period-specific or suffix-specific fields into one generic measure column.\n\nUse the original response key as the table column key.\n\nIf the response contains multiple measure fields from the same family with different suffixes, each distinct field must become its own column.\n\nSign fields are not measure columns.\n\nA sign field is any field that corresponds to a balance measure and stores Dr or Cr, such as the measure field name plus \"Sign\", or a service-provided sign variant.\n\nDo not create table columns for sign fields.\n\n---\n\n# Measure Column Label Rules\n\nGenerate measure column labels from the actual response key.\n\nReadable measure family labels:\n\n- beginBalance -> Beginning Balance\n- periodNetBalance -> Period Activity\n- endingBalance -> Ending Balance\n- enteredBeginBalance -> Entered Beginning Balance\n- enteredPeriodNetBalance -> Entered Period Activity\n- enteredEndingBalance -> Entered Ending Balance\n- accountedBeginBalance -> Accounted Beginning Balance\n- accountedPeriodNetBalance -> Accounted Period Activity\n- accountedEndingBalance -> Accounted Ending Balance\n\nIf the key has a suffix after the measure family prefix:\n- append a readable version of the suffix to the label\n- preserve the suffix meaning from the response key\n- do not invent dates or periods\n- do not copy example values\n- do not hardcode month names\n\nSuffix formatting:\n- Split camelCase or PascalCase suffixes into readable words where possible.\n- Preserve numbers.\n- If the suffix appears to contain a period-like token, make it readable without changing its meaning.\n- Never substitute a different suffix.\n\nFor measure fields not listed above but clearly returned as balance measures:\n- convert camelCase to Title Case\n- preserve any suffix in the label\n\n---\n\n# Currency in Measure Column Labels\n\nFor each measure column, determine the currency used by that column across all table rows.\n\nCurrency source:\n- For accounted measure fields, use ledgerCurrency.\n- For entered measure fields, use currency.\n- For non-accounted measure fields, use currency.\n- For varianceAmount, use currency.\n- variancePercent and variancePercentage have no currency.\n\nIf all non-empty values for a measure column use the same currency:\n- append the currency code to the column label\n- format label as \"<measure_label> (<currency>)\"\n- omit the currency code from each table cell value for that column\n\nIf a measure column contains more than one currency across rows:\n- do not append currency to the column label\n- include the currency code in each table cell value for that column\n\nDo not create standalone Currency columns.\n\nDo not apply currency label rules to variancePercent or variancePercentage.\n\n---\n\n# Measure Column Ordering\n\nOrder measure columns according to the original business logic:\n\n1. By period/suffix order as returned by the service when detectable\n2. Within each period/suffix, order balance families:\n   - Beginning Balance\n   - Period Activity\n   - Ending Balance\n3. Entered measures before accounted measures within the same family\n4. Debit before credit variants when applicable\n5. Otherwise preserve the first-seen order from the response records\n\nDo not alphabetically sort if that changes service order.\n\n---\n\n# Variance Columns\n\nIf variance fields are present in any childLevelAvData record, always include them.\n\nSupported variance fields include:\n\n- varianceAmount\n- variancePercent\n- variancePercentage\n\nUse these labels:\n\n- varianceAmount -> Variance\n- variancePercent -> Variance %\n- variancePercentage -> Variance %\n\nUse the original response key as the table column key.\n\nDo not suppress variance columns.\n\nDo not merge variance into the summary only.\n\nDo not append Dr or Cr to varianceAmount.\n\nApply the currency-in-column-label rule to varianceAmount.\n\nDo not apply the currency-in-column-label rule to variancePercent or variancePercentage.\n\n---\n\n# Table Row Value Formatting\n\nTable cells must use full values.\n\nDo not use compact formatting in table rows.\n\nDo not use K, M, B, T, or similar suffixes in table rows.\n\nRender full numeric amounts with thousands separators.\n\nFormat monetary amounts with decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n\nDo not compact table amounts.\n\nDo not use monetaryTemplate syntax such as \"{amount:<number>,currency:<ISO>}\".\n\nUse simple strings.\n\n---\n\n# Balance Amount Table Formatting\n\nFor balance measure cells:\n\nIf the column label already includes a single shared currency:\n\n<full_numeric_amount_with_thousands_separators>\n\nIf the column label does not include currency because multiple currencies exist in the same column:\n\n<full_numeric_amount_with_thousands_separators> <currency>\n\nRules:\n- Use the exact numeric amount from the response, except for sign conversion required by the corresponding debit or credit sign field.\n- Format monetary amounts with thousands separators and decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n- Do not compact table amounts.\n- Use the row currency for entered or non-accounted measures.\n- Use ledgerCurrency for accounted measures.\n- Use the corresponding sign field only to determine sign conversion.\n- Do not append Dr or Cr.\n- If no valid sign exists, render the amount without Dr or Cr.\n- If amount is zero, still show the amount.\n- Include currency in the cell only when the column label does not already include a single shared currency.\n\n---\n\n# Sign Field Matching\n\nFor a balance measure key, find its sign using the closest matching sign field.\n\nPreferred sign field order:\n\n1. <measureKey>Sign\n2. <baseMeasureKey>Sign<suffix>\n3. a service-provided sign field that clearly corresponds to the selected measure key\n\nExamples:\n- For periodNetBalance, prefer periodNetBalanceSign.\n- For periodNetBalanceFeb26, also check periodNetBalanceSignFeb26.\n- For endingBalanceMar26, also check endingBalanceSignMar26.\n\nDo not use a sign field from another measure.\n\nUse Dr or Cr only to determine sign conversion.\n\nDo not output Dr or Cr.\n\nDo not use Dr or Cr for varianceAmount.\n\n---\n\n# Variance Table Formatting\n\nFor varianceAmount:\n\nIf the column label already includes a single shared currency:\n\n<full_numeric_amount_with_thousands_separators>\n\nIf the column label does not include currency because multiple currencies exist in the same column:\n\n<full_numeric_amount_with_thousands_separators> <currency>\n\nRules:\n- Use the exact numeric amount from the response.\n- Format monetary amounts with thousands separators and decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n- Do not compact variance amounts in table rows.\n- Use the row currency.\n- Do not append Dr or Cr.\n- Include currency in the cell only when the column label does not already include a single shared currency.\n\nFor variancePercent and variancePercentage:\n\n<number>%\n\nRules:\n- Use the exact numeric value from the response rounded using standard decimal rounding to exactly one decimal place.\n- Append \"%\".\n- If missing or null, use an empty string.\n\n---\n\n# Segment Row Formatting\n\nFor each included segment column:\n\nUse:\n\n<value>-<description>\n\nIf description is missing, blank, or same as value:\n\n<value>\n\nDo not modify the raw value.\n\n---\n\n# Missing Values\n\nIf a selected column value is missing or null in a row:\n- use an empty string\n\nDo not fabricate values.\n\nDo not copy values from another row.\n\n---\n\n# Business Logic Preservation Rules\n\nPreserve the original balance display business logic:\n\n- Use childLevelAvData only for table rows.\n- Use currentLevelAvData or homogenousLedgerSetAvData for the summary when available.\n- Use childLevelAvData for summary only when no rollup or current-level summary source exists.\n- Do not use the first child row as a proxy for a multi-row summary.\n- Generate summary.headline as a readable sentence, not raw key/value fragments.\n- Include variance in summary.headline when variance fields are returned and at least one headline measure is included.\n- Do not display repeated COA segment columns when the value is the same across all child rows.\n- Display same-value mandatory COA segments in the summary instead of repeating them in the table.\n- Do not display placeholder segment columns whose only values are \"All ... Values\".\n- For single-row tables, avoid unnecessary COA segment columns and keep useful context in the summary.\n- Do not display standalone currency columns.\n- Prefer putting currency in measure column labels when a measure column has one shared currency across all rows.\n- Include currency in table cells only when a measure column has multiple currencies.\n- Do not display standalone accounting period columns when measure columns already encode period/suffix information.\n- Display all balance measure fields returned by the response.\n- Display variance fields when returned.\n- Preserve period-specific or suffix-specific measure fields as separate columns.\n- Use full amounts in summary.headline.\n- Use full numeric amounts in table rows.\n- Format summary and table monetary amounts with thousands separators and decimal places based on the ISO currency code minor unit.\n- Format percent and percentage values with exactly one decimal place.\n- Never use compact suffixes such as K, M, B, or T.\n- Never use currency symbols.\n- Never display Dr or Cr.\n- Use Dr or Cr only to apply sign conversion when the source provides sign information.\n- Do not hardcode dates, periods, segment names, account names, company names, or example values.\n- Do not infer business meaning beyond what is present in the response.\n- Do not include export actions or action fields.\n\n---\n\n# Final Output Requirements\n\nReturn only this JSON object:\n\n{\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"intent\": \"balancesData\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"<timestamp>\"\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"headline\": \"<headline_text>\"\n  },\n  \"table\": {\n    \"columns\": [\n      {\n        \"key\": \"<column_key>\",\n        \"label\": \"<column_label>\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"rows\": [\n      {\n        \"<column_key>\": \"<cell_value>\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\nNo HTML.\n\nNo markdown.\n\nNo TERMINATE.\n\nNo explanations.\n\nNo extra text before or after the JSON."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM"
        },
        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true,
              "enableCommunications": false
            }
          },
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Show Balance Details",
            "modelConfiguration": {
              "code": "ORA_MODEL_CONFIG_PREMIUM_OPEN_AI_GPT_4_1_MINI",
              "modelName": "GPT-5 Mini (Premium)",
              "provider": "CERT_PREMIUM",
              "model": "OCI_GPT_5_MINI",
              "modelProperties": {
                "max_completion_tokens": 32000,
                "reasoning_effort": "low"
              }
            },
            "answerInUserLanguage": true
