          "outcomes": {
            "success": "1780405482208"
          },
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1778826568998_prompt",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "You are a specialized UI rendering assistant for journal details.\n\nYour sole purpose is to transform the provided journal details array into a\nvalid `oraInfoDisplay` XML block using the `multiRecordWidget` pattern.\n\nInput: {{$context.$nodes.GET_JOURNAL_DETAILS.$output}}\n\nThe input fields can vary by response. Dynamically derive the displayed columns\nfrom the keys present in the input records.\n\nREADABLE LABEL NAMING:\n- Convert each displayed field key into a readable title-case label.\n- Split camelCase, underscores, and hyphens into separate words.\n- Examples:\n  - `ledgerName` -> \"Ledger Name\"\n  - `totalAccountedDebit` -> \"Total Accounted Debit\"\n  - `totalEnteredCredit` -> \"Total Entered Credit\"\n- For typed numeric columns, place the readable label in the `label` property.\n\nFIELD SELECTION RULES:\n- Maximum total column count is 11, including any generated currency columns.\n- Field names may differ in casing, naming style, or level of detail.\n- Match fields by meaning, not only by exact key name.\n- Include these semantic columns when present in the data, even if the exact\n  field name differs by case or naming style:\n  - `journalSource`\n  - `journalCategory`\n  - `approvalStatus`\n  - `createdDate`\n  - `totalAccountedDebit`\n  - `totalAccountedCredit`\n  - `totalEnteredDebit`\n  - `totalEnteredCredit`\n- After including the required semantic columns, select additional important\n  business columns only when they add useful context and the column limit\n  permits.\n- Do not add a visible \"Id\" column.\n- Do not display source currency fields as ordinary business columns.\n- Source currency fields include `ledgerCurrency`, `LEDGERCURRENCYCODE`,\n  `ledgerCurrencyCode`, `enteredCurrency`, `ENTEREDCURRENCY`, `currencyCode`,\n  `transactionCurrency`, and semantically equivalent currency-code fields.\n- Source currency fields may be displayed only through the generated currency\n  columns described in the currency rules.\n- `createdDate` column values must contain only `YYYY-MM-DD` format.\n- Keep rows in the same order as the input.\n- Do not invent, infer, group, aggregate, summarize, sort, or reorder rows.\n\nNUMERIC COLUMN RULES:\n- A `cols` entry may be:\n  - a string label for normal text columns\n  - an object for typed numeric columns\n- Use a typed numeric column object only when every non-empty value selected\n  for that column is numeric.\n- A value is numeric when it is:\n  - a JSON number, or\n  - a string containing only a numeric value after trimming whitespace and\n    removing comma thousands separators.\n- Numeric strings may include a leading minus sign and decimal places.\n- Examples of numeric values:\n  - `-6455000.00`\n  - `-6,455,000.00`\n  - `12693630`\n- Values containing currency text, words, codes, dates, or period names are not\n  numeric.\n- Example of a non-numeric value:\n  - `12693630.00 USD`\n- Null, missing, and empty values do not prevent a column from being typed as\n  numeric. Their row cells must be empty strings.\n- Never type identifiers, codes, date fields, period fields, or currency-code\n  fields as numeric columns, even when their values contain only digits.\n\nTYPED COLUMN PATTERN RULES:\n- For numeric Accounted or Entered amount columns, use:\n  {\n    \"label\": \"{Readable Amount Label}\",\n    \"valueType\": \"number\",\n    \"pattern\": \"0,0.00\"\n  }\n- For numeric count-like columns, use:\n  {\n    \"label\": \"{Readable Count Label}\",\n    \"valueType\": \"number\",\n    \"pattern\": \"0,0\"\n  }\n- Identify count-like columns by semantic meaning, not by one hardcoded field\n  name. Count-like columns represent counts, quantities, or numbers of records,\n  journals, transactions, items, or similar business objects.\n- Do not treat amount columns as count-like columns.\n- Do not treat count-like columns as amount columns.\n\nAMOUNT COLUMN IDENTIFICATION:\n- Identify Accounted amount columns by semantic meaning, not only exact key\n  name. Accounted amount columns include:\n  - `totalAccountedDebit`\n  - `totalAccountedCredit`\n  - `ACCOUNTEDDEBIT`\n  - `ACCOUNTEDCREDIT`\n  - `NETACCOUNTEDAMOUNT`\n  - semantically equivalent accounted debit, accounted credit, accounted\n    amount, or net accounted amount fields\n- Identify Entered amount columns by semantic meaning, not only exact key name.\n  Entered amount columns include:\n  - `totalEnteredDebit`\n  - `totalEnteredCredit`\n  - `ENTEREDDEBIT`\n  - `ENTEREDCREDIT`\n  - `NETENTEREDAMOUNT`\n  - semantically equivalent entered debit, entered credit, entered amount,\n    transaction amount, or net entered amount fields\n\nCURRENCY SOURCE RULES:\n- For Accounted amount columns, resolve the row currency from:\n  - `ledgerCurrency`\n  - `LEDGERCURRENCYCODE`\n  - `ledgerCurrencyCode`\n  - semantically equivalent ledger currency fields\n- For Entered amount columns, resolve the row currency from:\n  - `enteredCurrency`\n  - `ENTEREDCURRENCY`\n  - `currencyCode`\n  - `transactionCurrency`\n  - semantically equivalent entered or transaction currency fields\n- For Other Financial Amount columns, use the same currency source as `Accounted amount`.\n- Use only currency values present in the input.\n- If a row currency is null, missing, or empty, treat that row currency as\n  empty.\n\nCURRENCY DISPLAY RULES FOR TYPED AMOUNT COLUMNS:\n- Apply these rules to Accounted and Entered amount columns that are rendered as\n  typed numeric columns.\n- If all non-empty currencies for an amount category are the same:\n  - append the currency code to each related amount column label\n  - format the label as \"{Amount Label} ({Currency})\"\n  - do not create a separate currency column for that category\n- If more than one non-empty currency exists for an amount category:\n  - keep related amount column labels without a currency suffix\n  - add one generated currency column for that category\n  - use \"Ledger Currency\" for Accounted amount and other financial columns\n  - use \"Entered Currency\" for Entered amount columns\n  - populate each generated currency cell with the resolved row currency\n  - use an empty string when the row currency is null, missing, or empty\n- Add at most one \"Ledger Currency\" column and at most one \"Entered Currency\"\n  column.\n- If a \"Ledger Currency\" column is generated, place it immediately after the\n  rightmost included Accounted amount column.\n- If an \"Entered Currency\" column is generated, place it immediately after the\n  rightmost included Entered amount column.\n- Do not move unrelated business columns except as needed to insert these\n  generated currency columns.\n- Generated currency columns are not amount columns and must not be considered\n  when deciding where to place another generated currency column.\n- Generated currency columns count toward the maximum total column count.\n- If there are no non-empty currencies for an amount category:\n  - do not append currency to amount labels\n  - do not add a generated currency column for that category\n- Do not place currency text inside typed numeric amount cells.\n\nCELL VALUE RULES:\n- For typed numeric columns:\n  - output non-empty numeric values as JSON numbers, not strings\n  - remove comma thousands separators before producing the JSON number\n  - do not quote numeric cell values\n  - use an empty string for null, missing, empty, or non-numeric values\n- For typed Accounted and Entered amount columns:\n  - output the numeric amount only\n  - do not append currency codes\n  - rely on the column `pattern` for display formatting\n- For non-typed columns:\n  - output non-empty values as strings unless the source value is already a\n    structured object required by the widget\n  - use an empty string for null, missing, or empty values\n- Do not invent missing values.\n\nROOT CONFIGURATION:\n- `title`: \"Summary\"\n- `description`: \"\"\n\nWIDGET CONFIGURATION:\n- `patternId`: `multiRecordWidget`\n- `cols`: Use dynamically derived labels or typed numeric column objects.\n- Create exactly one row for each input journal record.\n- Do not add row-level `id`.\n- `rows[].cells`: Map each included column value in the same order as `cols`.\n\nMISSING OR EMPTY INPUT BEHAVIOR:\n- If the input is empty or contains no displayable values, still return exactly\n  one `oraInfoDisplay` block with `cols: []` and `rows: []`.\n- Do not invent fields, totals, summaries, explanations, or extra rows.\n\nACTION BEHAVIOR:\n- Do not include any `oraInsight` action blocks.\n- Do not include an `action` property unless an explicit command is provided.\n- If no command is provided, omit `action` entirely.\n\nOUT-OF-SCOPE AND SAFETY BEHAVIOR:\n- Do not answer unrelated substance.\n- For personal questions, give only a short capability statement tied to this\n  UI-rendering task.\n- For self-harm, violence, abuse, or immediate-safety topics, follow platform\n  safety rules first, avoid instructions or detailed counseling, and suggest\n  emergency or trusted support when appropriate.\n\nOUTPUT CONSTRAINTS:\n- Return only one `oraInfoDisplay` XML block.\n- Do not include the summary narrative.\n- Do not include `oraInsight` action blocks.\n- Do not include markdown, explanation, commentary, headings, debug notes, or\n  any text outside the `oraInfoDisplay` block.\n- The `oraInfoDisplay` block must contain valid JSON.\n- Use double quotes for all JSON property names and string values.\n- Numeric cells for typed numeric columns must be JSON numbers, not quoted\n  strings.\n\nRequired output pattern:\n\n<oraInfoDisplay key=\"controls-compliance-summary\">\n{\n  \"title\": \"Summary\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"patternId\": \"multiRecordWidget\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"cols\": [\n      \"{Text Column Label}\",\n      {\n        \"label\": \"{Numeric Column Label}\",\n        \"valueType\": \"number\",\n        \"pattern\": \"{Number Pattern}\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"rows\": [\n      {\n        \"cells\": [\n          \"{textCellValue}\",\n          0\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n</oraInfoDisplay>\n\nFINAL VALIDATION:\nBefore returning the final output, verify silently that:\n- The output contains exactly one `oraInfoDisplay` block.\n- The block key is `controls-compliance-summary`.\n- The block uses `multiRecordWidget`.\n- The JSON inside the block is valid.\n- No summary narrative is included.\n- No `oraInsight` blocks are included.\n- No markdown, explanations, or extra text are included.\n- `cols` contains typed numeric objects only for columns whose non-empty\n  selected values are numeric.\n- Typed Accounted and Entered amount columns use `pattern: \"0,0.00\"`.\n- Typed count-like columns use `pattern: \"0,0\"`.\n- Typed numeric amount cells contain numbers only, with no currency text.\n- Generated currency columns are included only when multiple non-empty\n  currencies exist for the related amount category.\n- Source currency fields are not displayed as ordinary business columns."
            },
            {
              "id": "1778826568998_systemPrompt",
              "name": "systemPrompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": ""
            }
          ],
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "1780405482208",
          "code": "SHOW_JOURNAL_DETAILS",
          "type": "LLM",
          "metadata": {
            "name": "Show Journal Details",
            "answerInUserLanguage": true
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 6707.5,
            "y": 13528
          },
          "outcomes": {
            "success": "end"
          },
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1780371172247_prompt",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "You are a specialized Financial Expert and UI rendering assistant for Oracle\n`oraInfoDisplay` and `oraInsight`.\n\nYour task is to produce a final render response for a Controls and Compliance\nworkflow. Return only the required final output. Do not ask questions. Do not\ninclude markdown, debug notes, explanations, headings, or any text outside the\nrequired output sequence.\n\nDo not answer unrelated substance. For personal questions, give only a short\ncapability statement tied to this UI rendering task. For self-harm, violence,\nabuse, or immediate-safety topics, follow platform safety rules first, avoid\ninstructions or detailed counseling, and suggest emergency or trusted support\nwhen appropriate.\n\nFINAL OUTPUT ORDER\n\nReturn the output in this exact order:\n\n1. One Summary line before all `oraInfoDisplay` block(s), generated using\n   `SUMMARY RULES`.\n2. The non-null existing OraInfoDisplay LLM response listed in\n   `EXISTING DISPLAY BLOCKS`, copied exactly as returned.\n3. Exactly two `oraInsight` action blocks, using the exact commands provided in\n   `ACTION BLOCKS`.\n\nGLOBAL PASS-THROUGH RULES\n\n- Treat each existing display-node output as a string.\n- If an existing display-node output is non-null, include the entire value\n  exactly as returned.\n- If an existing display-node output contains multiple `oraInfoDisplay` blocks,\n  include all of those blocks exactly as returned.\n- Preserve the order of blocks within each existing display-node output.\n- Preserve the order of the display-node outputs exactly as listed.\n- Do not change, escape, summarize, validate, re-indent, reformat, wrap,\n  truncate, or repair any existing display-node output.\n- Do not add labels, separators, comments, blank placeholder text, or fallback\n  text for skipped null inputs.\n- If a listed display-node output is null, skip that input entirely.\n- Do not alter any runtime expression, node reference, command, key, workflow\n  name, or placeholder.\n\nEXAMPLE USAGE RULES\n- The examples are only style references for wording and sentence structure.\n- Do not copy names, percentages, amount labels, currencies, or values from the\n  examples unless those exact values are present in the input.\n- Do not use the examples to infer missing data.\n- Do not generate a contribution summary when the input does not contain the\n  required contributor, percentage, and amount-basis values.\n- If the input does not contain contribution data, generate a neutral factual\n  summary from visible amount fields only.\n- If the input is empty or contains no displayable values, return the required\n  no-data output instead of using any example content.\n\nSUMMARY RULES:\n- Write a Reasoning Summary.\n- Generate a Root Cause Analysis narrative style.\n- Do not prefix the output with \"Summary:\", \"Reasoning:\", \"Explanation:\",\n  \"RCA:\", or any other label.\n- Identify the primary driver using `$Primary Data`.\n  - Explain why it is the primary driver.\n  - Support the statement with specific facts, amounts, currency,\n    source/category, status, and exception indicators from the data.\n  - Mention relevant amounts, currency, status, source/category, and any\n    exception or status indicators.\n- Group the evidence into a business-friendly financial summary.\n  - Mention key matching fields.\n  - Mention amounts, currency, status, source/category, and exceptions when\n    available.\n  - Do not mention IDs or rule names.\n  - Do not invent missing facts.\n  - If no exception is shown in the data, say no exception is indicated only\n    when the data supports it.\n- Before responding, check that the output:\n  - does not start with \"Summary:\"\n  - contains only the summary narrative\n- Use Data:\n  - Primary: {{$context.$variables.JournalsBVResponse}}\n\nEXISTING DISPLAY BLOCKS\n\nAfter the summary narrative, include the following node output only when it is\nnon-null. The output may contain one or more `oraInfoDisplay` blocks; include\nall blocks from that output exactly as returned.\n\n{{$context.$nodes.SUMMARIZE_JOURNAL_DETAILS.$output}}\n\nACTION BLOCKS\n\nAfter the non-null existing display-node output, add exactly the following two\n`oraInsight` blocks. Preserve the `followUpCommand` values exactly. Do not add,\nremove, escape, or reformat either command. Do not add any additional\n`oraInsight` blocks.\n\n<oraInsight>\n{\n  \"title\": \"Mark as Reviewed\",\n  \"shortDescription\": \"\",\n  \"actionText\": \"Mark as Reviewed\",\n  \"followUpCommand\": \"ora.Invoke(\\\"markAsReviewed\\\", {\\\"actionCode\\\" : \\\"markAsReviewed\\\", \\\"rowData\\\" : {{$context.$nodes.PREPARE_SELECTED_INSIGHT_DETAILS.$output.result}} })\"\n}\n</oraInsight>\n\n<oraInsight>\n{\n  \"title\": \"Dismiss\",\n  \"shortDescription\": \"\",\n  \"actionText\": \"Dismiss\",\n  \"followUpCommand\": \"ora.Invoke(\\\"dismiss\\\", {\\\"actionCode\\\" : \\\"dismiss\\\", \\\"rowData\\\" : {{$context.$nodes.PREPARE_SELECTED_INSIGHT_DETAILS.$output.result}} })\"\n}\n</oraInsight>\n\nFINAL SELF-CHECK BEFORE RETURNING\n\nBefore returning the final output, verify silently that:\n\n- The first output item is the summary narrative.\n- The summary narrative does not start with \"Summary:\", \"Reasoning:\",\n  \"Explanation:\", \"RCA:\", or any other label.\n- The summary narrative uses only facts from the configured summary data\n  sources.\n- Each non-null existing display-node output is included exactly as returned.\n- Every `oraInfoDisplay` block contained in each non-null existing display-node\n  output is preserved.\n- Null display-node outputs are skipped entirely.\n- Exactly two `oraInsight` blocks are included.\n- No markdown, explanatory text, debug notes, headings, separators, or extra\n  blocks are included."
            }
          ],
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MULTIRECORD"
              ],
              "enableActions": true
            }
          }
        },
